CatDescriptText: According to city directories, Stanley's Tavern, a restaurant, was located at 1506 Wylie Avenue in 1945.  It was owned by William Stanley.  This photograph seems to show a side entrance, street number 63, possibly off Fullerton Street.  The restaurant has an electric sign with its name, images of a martini glass and coffee cup, and a clock reading approximately 11:30.  Street car tracks appear in the foreground.
TitMainTitle: Stanley's Tavern at Fullerton Street and Wylie Avenue, Hill District
